sentences: Natsumi Kon (昆 夏美, Kon Natsumi, born 28 June 1991) is a Japanese musical actress and singer.
She liked to sing from a young age, and also to play and dance, and from 2003 to 2006 she belonged to the Children's Theatre Ōkina Yume and acted primarily in leading roles.
In 2009, when was on third grade high school, she was selected as the role of the girl Anne in the music play Anne of Green Gables sponsored by the DPI-NGO UN Classical Live Association.
In 2010, she studied at the Senzoku Gakuen High School Music School from the Senzoku Gakuen College of Music Faculty of Music Musical Course.

She passed the audition of Toho Entertainment in 2011 while enrolled in her second year of college, and in the heroine audition of the musical Roméo et Juliette which received in less than a month after entering the office, she was selected as Juliette from among many candidates, which made her major work pro debut.
